{"id":17296,"date":"2013-12-24T20:36:11","date_gmt":"2013-12-24T16:36:11","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.dailyhadithonline.com\/?p=17296"},"modified":"2023-03-09T14:41:48","modified_gmt":"2023-03-09T10:41:48","slug":"better-forgive-hudud-if-possible","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/12\/24\/better-forgive-hudud-if-possible\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Hudud: The Prophet reluctantly punishes a thief"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: I will tell you about the first man to have his hand cut. He was brought for stealing, and the order was given to cut his hand. The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, was so upset his face changed color as if it were covered with dust. They said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, do you dislike cutting his hand?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<b>What could prevent me? Do not help Satan against one of your brothers! The leader must carry out a case of legal punishment brought to him. Verily, Allah Almighty is forgiving and He loves forgiveness<\/b>.\u201d Then, the Prophet recited the verse, \u201c<b>Let them pardon and overlook. Would you not love for Allah to forgive you? Allah is surely forgiving and merciful<\/b>.\u201d (24:22)<\/p>\n<p>Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 4167<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <i>Hasan<\/i> (fair) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p align=\"right\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0633\u0652\u0639\u064f\u0648\u062f\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0646\u0651\u0650\u064a \u0644\u064e\u0623\u064e\u0630\u0652\u0643\u064f\u0631\u064f \u0623\u064e\u0648\u0651\u064e\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0637\u064e\u0639\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0623\u064f\u062a\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0628\u0650\u0633\u064e\u0627\u0631\u0650\u0642\u064d \u0641\u064e\u0623\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e \u0628\u0650